New figure.

This is the phase diagram we talked about.
Here the idea is to give a complete picture on which parameters lead you through a martensitic transformation, to the GS.


To make this, I plotted the charge order parameter for the last frame of each one of the simulations, averaged across realizations, and plotted this as a "heatmap". This is typically a smooth plot.

i realized that indeed we have three main regions
1. Martensitic
2. Partially ordered stuff
3. Complete mess

So I kind of made a more discrete version by filtering values, and that is the plot to the left.
 NOTAS
Esta figura es conveniente hacerla de dos columnas para poder incluir tanto el diagrama de fase, como algunos zooms a las regiones en como se ven
